sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K300983
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: BBa_K300000 construction intermediate (provided by Mr Gene)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part has been provided by Mr Gene synthesis service and it has been used to construct <partinfo>BBa_K300982</partinfo> plasmid. On the other hand, <partinfo>BBa_K300982</partinfo> was used to construct <partinfo>BBa_K300000</partinfo> BioBrick integrative base vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lorenzo Pasotti, Matteo Meroso, Nicolo' Politi, Paolo Magni
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: See <partinfo>BBa_K300000</partinfo> for details about the design of this part.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0033
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weaker RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strengths relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-3" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
